I always appreciate Jun singing Korean and Japanese, but I noticed when he sings in his native language, he voice sounds more comfortable, confident, and he also adds another layer of emotion in his tone. I think maybe only native Chinese speakers can identify this somehow. 
Junhui is so talented. We stan. He deserves the world.

text:
I was reading a very sad story right now ... This song comforted me... I love Seventeen and will always do... I always wished to have brothers like you all in real life... But I guess even if I can't meet you everyday or talk to you... You always make my day the brightest... I feel the sincere comfort everytime I listen to your music... I love you my brothers... As a single girl child I sometimes feel the need for a big bro... When other people talk about their siblings, l just feel a little jealous... But now that I have you all, not just one but THIRTEEN BIG BROS... I can proudly say that I have 13 brothers and my CARAT FAMILY to always comfort me, make me laugh and sometimes even cry because of their sincere feelings...My 13 Diamond Brothers... I love you~ 
Thank you for helping me in my hard times... Seranghe~
 And for my Carat family...
Caranghe~

its been a long time since i checked out seventeen .. today i was soo stressed and my anxiety was peaking so badly cos of an assignment that i had to do.. and i saw this on my recommended and put this on just for the sake of it..

i dont know how to explain how it felt... it was like his voice and the music was hugging me tightly after like 4 to 7 hours of intense anxiety.. and somehow during the first 20 secs itself, i could feel the anxiety draining from my body..and almost 90 percent of it was gone that I almost fell asleep listening to it cos i was so at peace.

i dont know if i explained it correctly but this song was really healing...

text:
English Trans 

Back to this port again, and I'm staying here without a reason
My heart is adventuring on mottled boat
Searching for the lost sandbar

Drifting with the waves of time
I opened my arms with force
Embracing so many ups and downs
But I still miss the way you look at me

I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I'm staring at the sea all alone again
Then turning back to find that you are no longer there
Leaving me to wander around aimlessly

I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I think back to the old times
There was so much emptiness besides you
Who else can teach me how to love?

Back to this endpoint again
I want to move forward too
Seeing so much of this world
My only regret would be that you are not there to share the moment with me

I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I'm staring at the sea all alone again
Then turning back to find that you are no longer there
Leaving me to wander around aimlessly

I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I think back to the old times
There was so much emptiness besides you
Who else can teach me how to love?

I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I'm staring at the sea all alone again
The tired silhouette is not mine
It's not the person I want you to see
I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I walked into the crowd alone
Other than depending on you
Who else can teach me courage?
There was so much emptiness besides you
Who else can teach me how to love?

author: @reply514
text:
Back to this port again, and I'm staying here without a reason
My heart is adventuring on mottled boat
Searching for the lost sandbar

Drifting with the waves of time
I opened my arms with force
Embracing so many ups and downs
But I still miss the way you look at me

I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I'm staring at the sea all alone again
Then turning back to find that you are no longer there
Leaving me to wander around aimlessly

I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I think back to the old times
There was so much emptiness besides you
Who else can teach me how to love?

Back to this endpoint again
I want to move forward too
Seeing so much of this world
My only regret would be that you are not there to share the moment with me

I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I'm staring at the sea all alone again
Then turning back to find that you are no longer there
Leaving me to wander around aimlessly

I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I think back to the old times
There was so much emptiness besides you
Who else can teach me how to love?

I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I'm staring at the sea all alone again
The tired silhouette is not mine
It's not the person I want you to see
I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I walked into the crowd alone
Other than depending on you
Who else can teach me courage?
There was so much emptiness besides you
Who else can teach me how to love?

author: @ayuannur9557
text:
The first one coming to me after I'm hearing Jun singing: OH MY GOD. IS IT A GREAT IMPROVEMENT I HEARD? BUT I NOTICED IT SINCE GOOD TO ME, THEN HIT AND ESPECIALLY FEAR! 
I remember something. Why do when Jun is talking, he sounds in a baritone and husky voice (especially when he's laughing) but when Jun is singing it sounds too tenor or like Japanese idol singer using nose-voice? 
Now Jun proved that he's been improved so much! I want to cry so much (but I'm fasting now). I remember in CHYZ that he has to received injections because his throat has been hurt so much. Jun, please take care of your throat and your healthy. I want to thank Pledis for releasing your cover, but I hope they take care of your body and mental health too. But I know something, you are so strong and have 4D personality. 

I'm watching Going Seventeen for you! Maybe this is weird, but I love your interaction with Boo Seungkwan. Seems he is real to you. I dont know about the reality, but in screens, it seems you're lonely and not many members genuinely liking you. Not all the times but I love the way you've been relax and joking around and can even dissing people. You're being true to yourself, and I'm proud of you. 

In my country, girls tend to pray so hard for the man they love. But I got broken heart so bad haha. Instead, your name is the one that I mention for improvement. After that, you became the grand center for Clap and I'm crying and screaming happily for like centuries. In Mama and KBS Award and GoSe, you played piano too! I was choking and feel so blue-pink feeling saw you playing piano beautifully! Then I watched you participating in Chao Yi Zhan Ji. I remember your friend said, "Junhui is known as a great dancer in his group, but he challenged himself to perform vocal. Isn't he great?" And I remember you cried at the concert when saying there's no member-deul and Carats. I cried too. 

 We're at the same age, I'm just 1 month older to you at 23rd May. So the past 5 years, I feel like I'm growing up with you too. From the quiet young handsome boy, to multitalented and real to yourself adult. I love you, My Faraway Friend, Wen Junhui. Thank you for inspiring me so much and giving me so much happiness. 
I want to see and meet you at the concert and fanmeeting. Hopefully the world conspired to do that. 

I know you have home in China, and I wish you can be with your family again. But I'm praying hard you will playing in a Korean drama, or especially in China again! After you're done with Seventeen, because you wont be in Seventeen and I'm painfully aware of that. I'm mentally preparing myself of Seventeen disbandment (and if any other member not renewaI their contract). I hope you will open an instagram acc and I can tell you how much you mean to me. watching your shenanigans and your selfie! I love your selfie and antiques too. ğŸ˜‚ I always thought do you have any girlfriend like the other idol and I'm giggling to myself because if you have, I would be cheering for you and your lover! 

Yes, I want to stay as Carat and as your faraway friend. Hopefully I can learn Mandarin to speak or talk to you! Thank you very much for your hardwork. It wont be forever, but lets stay together for a long time! ğŸ’—ğŸ’

.

Love, 

a.a.a

author: @cherryvt4815
text:
READ til End.
One thing that I want to say. 

THANK YOU, PLEDIS! 
They're so many in their group. But only got few lines. 
We all knew that Jun is part of the Performance Team. #HOSHI #THE8 #DINO showed their dance  routined and creativity.. And has their dance solo uploaded. But others are wondering, asking this question. If He's the lead dancer of SVT, and part of the performance team. Then why Jun is singing than Dancing??? Well, the fact that I know is that., if you nourished your skill/talent you'll get better on it. This will boost your passion when you keep practicing. And a lot of us knew, that when he was a little kid back then. Music already hits him. It was already there. He loves playing piano, and I think he also plays violin. Although I didn't see him doing that yet. But maybe in the future. Well let me show you a little bit of their background. #HOSHI who got inspired of Shinee when he was young. He started his own piece. tried to create unique DANCE moves, and ended up joining in a Dance competition and they won. 

#DINO - when he was a kid. DANCE is his passion. His father own a dance studio.. so it means, His father is good dancer too. The one who taught him. Until he got inspired more to the King of Pop. #MichaelJackson.  He keeps on practicing while he was a kid. Til he gets better and  better. Well, you cant deny that coz you've all see him Dancing right? And lastly
..

#THE8 (Minghao) we all knew this. That when he was a kid. He fond of B-boying. Hiphop style.. which means DANCE is his passion. Until he wants to learn more, more than just dance breaking. And all of us witnessed that. He improves a lot. 

So you see,  JUN is totally different among the 3. he grew up as a Music lover. Fond of Singing and playing instruments. So I hope this helps you to understand. If ever some of you would like to add. Just comment below. 

And ohh by the way. We also knew that Jun is a good DANCER. Well, training days make him good at it. He's a martial artist and a wushu guy. Its easy to adapt some routine if you kinda flexible. And one more thing, determination. Thats what makes him good into DANCING.

author: @meltedpoo
text:
He probably won't read this but I hope Jun is surrounded by people who recognize his worth forever. I hope he realizes that he is so, so beautiful inside and out. I know that we will only ever see a small part of idols' personalities but what little we see of Jun is enough to show that he has such a kind and pure heart and always striving for happiness. Surrounded by members who are talented, louder and confident, it's often easy to overlook Jun because he's so quiet but I hope he knows that there are fans out there who love him and appreciate him and see his talents. Whatever path Jun pursues, I want to support him because he deserves it. I love his dance and his voice the most and I want to see more of it. 
My thoughts are all over the place but I just had to get it out there that I love Jun and his dedication to his art so much. Im emotional.

Had to search the translated lyrics so here it goes:

Back to this port again, and I'm staying here without a reason

Searching for the lost sandbar

I opened my arms with force
Embracing so many ups and downs

I don't necessarily need you back

Leaving me to wander around aimlessly

I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I think back to the old times
There was so much emptiness besides you
Who else can teach me how to love?

Back to this endpoint again

Seeing so much of this world

Leaving me to wander around aimlessly

I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I think back to the old times
There was so much emptiness besides you
Who else can teach me how to love?

The tired silhouette is not mine

Who else can teach me courage?

text:
Lyrics Translation:
Back to this port again, and I'm staying here without a reason
My heart is adventuring on mottled boat
Searching for the lost sandbar

Drifting with the waves of time
I opened my arms with force
Embracing so many ups and downs
But I still miss the way you look at me

I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I'm staring at the sea all alone again
Then turning back to find that you are no longer there
Leaving me to wander around aimlessly

I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I think back to the old times
There was so much emptiness besides you
Who else can teach me how to love?

Back to this endpoint again
I want to move forward too
Seeing so much of this world
My only regret would be that you are not there to share the moment with me

I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I'm staring at the sea all alone again
Then turning back to find that you are no longer there
Leaving me to wander around aimlessly

I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I think back to the old times
There was so much emptiness besides you
Who else can teach me how to love?

I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I'm staring at the sea all alone again
The tired silhouette is not mine
It's not the person I want you to see
I don't necessarily need you back
It's only when I walked into the crowd alone
Other than depending on you
Who else can teach me courage?
There was so much emptiness besides you
Who else can teach me how to love?
